<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="566" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Woodford</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-03-28"><hi rend="italic">March 28,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your cable 27th received. Full self-government with indemnity would mean
                            Cuban independence. As to other matters see Sunday’s telegram. Very
                            important to have definite agreement for determining peace after
                            armistice, if negotiations pending same fail to reach satisfactory
                            conclusions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>